Class GenericType<T>

java.lang.Object
com.github.cowwoc.requirements10.java.GenericType<T>
Type Parameters:
T - the type of the class modelled by the GenericType object. For example, the type of String.class is GenericType<String>.
public abstract class GenericType<T> extends Object
A reference to a type that may contain type parameters. Based on Neal Gafter's blog post.

Sample usage: 

  GenericType<List<Integer>> type = new GenericType<List<Integer>>(){};
  Object unknown = List.of(1, 2, 3);
  List<Integer> actual = requireThat(value, "actual").isList(type).getActual();
